    <title>CoordConv</title>
    <url>/2020/03/31/CoordConv/</url>
    <content><![CDATA[<p>论文：<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1807.03247" target="_blank" rel="noopener">An Intriguing Failing of Convolutional Neural Networks and the CoordConv Solution</a> (NeurIPS 2018)</p><p>源码：<a href="https://github.com/uber-research/coordconv" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://github.com/uber-research/coordconv</a></p><a id="more"></a>

<h2 id="1-摘要"><a href="#1-摘要" class="headerlink" title="1. 摘要"></a>1. 摘要</h2><p>实验发现，卷积神经网络在坐标变换问题中表现不佳。因此，这篇论文提出了名为 <code>CoordConv</code> 的解决方案。该解决方案通过使用额外的坐标通道使卷积可以访问其自身的输入坐标而起作用。在不牺牲普通卷积的计算和参数效率的情况下，CoordConv 允许网络根据最终任务的要求学习完整的平移不变性或不同程度的平移依赖性。</p>
<h2 id="2-结构"><a href="#2-结构" class="headerlink" title="2. 结构"></a>2. 结构</h2><p><img src="/images/202003/CoordConv/fig1.png" width="512"></p>
<p>CoordConv 层可以实现为标准卷积的简单扩展，其中实例化了额外的通道并填充了坐标信息，然后将它们按通道级联到输入特征图并应用到标准卷积层中。具体而言，$i$ 坐标通道是一个形状为 $w\times h$ 的矩阵，其第一行填充为 0，第二行填充为 1，第三行填充为 2，依此类推。$j$ 坐标通道类似，但列填充为常数值而不是行。在所有实验中，$i$ 和 $j$ 的坐标值都进行了线性缩放，以使它们落在 $[-1,1]$ 范围内。对于二维卷积，$(i,j)$ 坐标足以完全指定一个输入像素，但是如果需要，还可以添加其他通道以使模型偏向于学习特定的解决方案。例如，使用第三条通道 $r$，其中 $r=\sqrt{(i-h/2)^2+(j-w/2)^2}$。</p>
<h2 id="3-代码实现"><a href="#3-代码实现" class="headerlink" title="3. 代码实现"></a>3. 代码实现</h2><p>这里基于 TensorFlow 1.x 和 TensorLayer 来实现 CoordConv。</p>
<figure class="highlight python"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="keyword">import</span> tensorflow <span class="keyword">as</span> tf</span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">from</span> tensorlayer.layers.core <span class="keyword">import</span> Layer</span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">from</span> tensorlayer <span class="keyword">import</span> logging</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="class"><span class="keyword">class</span> <span class="title">AddCoordLayer</span><span class="params">(Layer)</span>:</span></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="function"><span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="title">__init__</span><span class="params">(</span></span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="function"><span class="params">        self,</span></span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="function"><span class="params">        prev_layer,</span></span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="function"><span class="params">        name=<span class="string">'add_coord_layer'</span>,</span></span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="function"><span class="params">    )</span>:</span></span><br><span class="line">        super(AddCoordLayer, self).__init__(prev_layer=prev_layer, name=name)</span><br><span class="line">        logging.info(<span class="string">"AddCoordLayer %s"</span> % (self.name))</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">        shape = self.inputs.get_shape().as_list()</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">        <span class="comment"># i</span></span><br><span class="line">        xx_ones = tf.ones([shape[<span class="number">0</span>], shape[<span class="number">1</span>]], dtype=tf.int32) <span class="comment"># e.g. (batch, 64)</span></span><br><span class="line">        xx_ones = tf.expand_dims(xx_ones, <span class="number">-1</span>)                   <span class="comment"># e.g. (batch, 64, 1)</span></span><br><span class="line">        xx_range = tf.tile(tf.expand_dims(</span><br><span class="line">            tf.range(shape[<span class="number">2</span>]), <span class="number">0</span>), [shape[<span class="number">0</span>], <span class="number">1</span>])              <span class="comment"># e.g. (batch, 64)</span></span><br><span class="line">        xx_range = tf.expand_dims(xx_range, <span class="number">1</span>)                  <span class="comment"># e.g. (batch, 1, 64)</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">        xx_channel = tf.matmul(xx_ones, xx_range)               <span class="comment"># e.g. (batch, 64, 64)</span></span><br><span class="line">        xx_channel = tf.expand_dims(xx_channel, <span class="number">-1</span>)             <span class="comment"># e.g. (batch, 64, 64, 1)</span></span><br><span class="line">        </span><br><span class="line">        <span class="comment"># j</span></span><br><span class="line">        yy_ones = tf.ones([shape[<span class="number">0</span>], shape[<span class="number">2</span>]], dtype=tf.int32) <span class="comment"># e.g. (batch, 64)</span></span><br><span class="line">        yy_ones = tf.expand_dims(yy_ones, <span class="number">1</span>)                    <span class="comment"># e.g. (batch, 1, 64)</span></span><br><span class="line">        yy_range = tf.tile(tf.expand_dims(</span><br><span class="line">            tf.range(shape[<span class="number">1</span>]), <span class="number">0</span>), [shape[<span class="number">0</span>], <span class="number">1</span>])              <span class="comment"># e.g. (batch, 64)</span></span><br><span class="line">        yy_range = tf.expand_dims(yy_range, <span class="number">-1</span>)                 <span class="comment"># e.g. (batch, 64, 1)</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">        yy_channel = tf.matmul(yy_range, yy_ones)               <span class="comment"># e.g. (batch, 64, 64)</span></span><br><span class="line">        yy_channel = tf.expand_dims(yy_channel, <span class="number">-1</span>)             <span class="comment"># e.g. (batch, 64, 64, 1)</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">        <span class="comment"># norm</span></span><br><span class="line">        xx_channel = tf.cast(xx_channel, <span class="string">'float32'</span>) / (shape[<span class="number">1</span>] - <span class="number">1</span>)</span><br><span class="line">        yy_channel = tf.cast(yy_channel, <span class="string">'float32'</span>) / (shape[<span class="number">2</span>] - <span class="number">1</span>)</span><br><span class="line">        xx_channel = xx_channel*<span class="number">2</span> - <span class="number">1</span>                           <span class="comment"># [-1,1]</span></span><br><span class="line">        yy_channel = yy_channel*<span class="number">2</span> - <span class="number">1</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">        self.outputs = tf.concat([self.inputs, xx_channel, yy_channel], <span class="number">-1</span>, name=name)</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">        self._add_layers(self.outputs)</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>]]></content>
      <categories>
        <category>深度学习</category>
      </categories>
      <tags>
        <tag>TensorFlow</tag>
        <tag>论文阅读</tag>
        <tag>TensorLayer</tag>
      </tags>
